<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-350-988  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 350 988.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronics Weekly  March 7 1990 n1498 p1(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>STC shake up puts jobs in jeopardy. (STC PLC restructures; cutsemployment)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pancucci, Dom.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>STC PLC's reorganization, including the subsidiary STCInternational Computers Ltd (ITL) and the research and developmentunit STC Technology Laboratories means layoffs and plant shutdowns1990.andP;  ITL's profits have increased partially through staffingcutbacks and more are expected.andP;  Approximately 100 jobs are to becut at STC Technology Laboratories by the end of 1990.andP;  The chipmaking plant at Foots Cray in Kent, UK may be closed and the NewSouthgate plant in north London may be sold in part.andP;  Profits roseabout 21 percent in 1989 for the company as a whole with someunits doing better than others.andP;  The layoffs are a result ofdeclines in orders for fiber optics equipment in the defense andtelecommunications industries.andP;  The reorganization is designed tostrengthen STC's commitment to software development as it movesaway from manufacturing.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   STC PLC (layoffs)STC International Computers Ltd. (layoffs)STC Technology Laboratories (layoffs).andO;Topic:     LayoffReorganizationPlant ShutdownsProfit.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>